The paper focuses on binary hashing for approximate nearest-neighbor search in information retrieval, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a new approach using techniques from classifier ensembles, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the objective function, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
